<section class="about-hero">

  <div class="about-content">

    <p class="subtitle">About</p>

    <h1>
      I don't photograph places.<br>
      I photograph the silence,<br>
      the light and the passing of time<br>
      that live within them.
    </h1>

    <div class="about-text">

      <p>
        I am drawn to waiting, atmosphere and those quiet moments that often remain unseen.
        The moments before the scene begins and long after it has ended.
      </p>

      <p>
        For me, photography has never been about documenting a place.
        It has always been about preserving the feeling of having been there.
      </p>

    </div>

  </div>

</section>

<section class="about-story">

  <div class="about-story-content">

    <p>
      I'm Fabrizio Vinciguerra, a Sicilian photographer born in 1983.
    </p>

    <p>
      Through photography I try to explore the relationship between light,
      memory and landscape.
    </p>

    <p>
      Forests, waterfalls, volcanic lands and distant places become the
      starting point for a simpler and more difficult search at the same time:
      transforming a space into an emotion and a moment into a memory.
    </p>

  </div>

</section>

<section class="awards-section">

  <p class="subtitle">Awards & Recognition</p>

  <h2>
    International recognition for stories shaped by light,
    silence and landscape.
  </h2>

  <div class="awards-text">

    <p>
      Between 2025 and 2026, several works by Fabrizio Vinciguerra reached
      the final stages of the international photography competition 35AWARDS.
    </p>

    <p>
      The competition brings together more than 112,000 photographers from over
      175 countries and receives more than 460,000 images every year.
    </p>

    <p>
      The photographs entered international shortlists and rankings, including
      Top 200 and Top 100 placements in the Landscape category, a Top 35 ranking
      among Italian photographers and the selection of one image for the official
      2025 35AWARDS catalogue.
    </p>

  </div>

